content.description: Follow a climb up the slab to an easy roof/corner climb this until you reach a large ledge. Then traverse up an easy slab with little gear to the right, next follow up the corner to the top (crux). The upper corner is totally the highlight of the route, starts with cool face climbing, then pumpy lie-backing and right as you start to think that there is no possible way that it will go you reach out right and find a rad glory jug. The rock gets a little bit kitty littery on ethier side of the dihedral but is good where it matters. The belays for every pitch have good stances. The slab start is a bit spooky but can be avoided by starting more left at the right-leaning crack that leads to the base of the dihedral.
content.location: On the NorWest side of Middle Lake. The start is at the north end of the buttress that looms over the lake.

climbs.name: Therapy direct
climbs.fa: Tagg Cole, Abe Lowham, Noah Lowham

content.description: Climb the obvious crack to the left of the slab start to Therapy Session into the right facing overhanging dihedral until you reach a small ledge. Then lead up the rest of the dihedral until you reach the big ledge on top of the dihedral. Then continue up the face heading slightly right towards a large ledge with a lot of trees, belay of a tree here. Then continue up the right facing corner until you reach top belay off a tree.
content.protection: Single from .2 to 3 works fine doubles of .75 to 3 would be better for people want more gear.
content.location: A variation of Therapy Session FA was done after
